The paper proposes a deep learning model that exploits Lagrangian duality to encourage the satisfaction of hard constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning, which is cs.LG. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization problems in engineering disciplines, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions energy networks, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with transprecision computing, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
